ce:section.ce:para:
Table 3 , in two separate sections, shows the images of the copper surface and the static contact angle (Interfacial Tension and Contact Angle Measurement Apparatus, Apex technologies, IFT-PDSA-02, Iran) with a measuring range of 1–175° and a 5 mega pixel camera values measured after the deposition of nanoparticles from the optimal nanofluids in a volume ratio of (50:50) deionized water to ethylene glycol. In order to measure the contact angle to better investigate the wettability of deionized water on the copper surface with optimal nanofluid deposition, we consider the droplet volume to be 2 microliter (
μ l
) and the settling size to be approximately equal to 10 s [9,66]. In addition, the details of the results obtained from static contact angle tests for nanofluids prepared in a (50:50) volume ratio of deionized water/ethylene glycol mixture are given in Table S1.
